# Books page

The `/books` page is a **generated reading list** of affiliate book links found in Prismic `sketchplanation` bodies (`geni.us`, `amzn.to`, `a.co`, Amazon).

## Build pipeline

| Command | When |
|---------|------|
| `npm run build:books` | Regenerate `data/books-index.json` after new sketches or curation edits |
| `npm run check:books-duplicates` | Fail if the built index has likely duplicate titles (also runs in CI after build) |
| `npm run fetch:book-authors` | Fill **missing** authors via affiliate URL → Open Library ISBN lookup |
| `npm run fetch:book-covers` | Download **missing** covers to `public/books/` (Open Library, then Google Books); writes `data/books-covers.json` |
| `predev` / `prebuild` | Runs `buildBooksIndex` automatically via `setup.mjs` |

**Commit to git:** `data/books-overrides.json`, `data/books-authors.json`, `data/books-covers.json`, images under `public/books/`, code in `utils/bookLinks.mjs`.

**Do not commit:** `data/books-index.json` (generated at build time).

## Curation files

### `data/books-overrides.json`

Keyed by normalised title (see `normalizeBookTitle` in `utils/bookLinks.mjs`).

Use for:

- `title` — fix messy link text the parser cannot infer
- `author` — override when link text does not include author
- `note` — optional personal note (plain prose on the page; only add when Jono writes them)
- `thumbnail` — cover image URL/path when you want to override a fetched cover
- `exclude: true` — non-book affiliate links (gear, games, etc.)

### `data/books-authors.json`

Flat map: `"normalised title": "Author Name"`.

Used when authors are wrong or missing after `fetch:book-authors`. Merged at build time; overrides win for `author` if both set.

### `data/books-covers.json`

Map of normalised title → `{ path, isbn, source }`. Paths are local (`/books/…`) under `public/books/`.

Filled by `fetch:book-covers` (manual; not part of every build). Merged at build time; overrides win for `thumbnail` if both set.

**Quality note:** Most covers currently come from Open Library (`-L` scans). Those are free and legal but often soft, stickered, or wrong-edition. Google Books usually has sharper publisher art, but anonymous requests hit rate limits / placeholder images. Set `GOOGLE_BOOKS_API_KEY` and re-run `npm run fetch:book-covers -- --upgrade` for better results, or drop replacement files into `public/books/` and point `thumbnail` in overrides. Flags: `--limit=30` to batch; `--retry-missing`; `--upgrade --only="title fragment|other"`; `--force`.

## Typical workflow

1. Publish sketch with affiliate book link in Prismic → deploy (or `npm run build:books`).
2. If title/author wrong → edit overrides or authors JSON → `npm run build:books`.
3. Batch author lookup → `npm run fetch:book-authors`, review diff, `npm run build:books`, commit JSON.
4. Batch covers → `npm run fetch:book-covers` (optionally `--limit=30`), spot-check images, replace any wrong files in `public/books/`, `npm run build:books`, commit JSON + images.

## Title parsing

Logic lives in `utils/bookLinks.mjs` (`parseBookLinkText`, `normalizeParsedTitle`):

- Strips `audiobook of`, `her book`, possessive `"X's book Y"`, leading `see` / `read`
- Merges duplicates by normalised title; prefers `geni.us` URLs
- Sorted by sketch reference count (most referenced first)

Add parser cases + tests in `tests/utils/bookLinks.test.js` for new edge cases.

## Analytics

Buy clicks fire `Books-buy-link` with `{ book, location }` where `location` is `title`, `author`, `button`, or `cover`.

